   "source": [
    "# Antenna Array"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "id": "efec1d0e",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import time\n",
    "\n",
    "import neoradium as nr"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "id": "0b128508",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 600x600 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# We first create an antenna element template. The 'AntennaPanel' class uses this template to \n",
    "# create the panel’s elements.\n",
    "elementTemplate = nr.AntennaElement(beamWidth=[65,65], maxAttenuation=30)\n",
    "\n",
    "# Now we create an antenna panel template. The 'AntennaArray' class uses this template to create the \n",
    "# panels of the antenna array.\n",
    "panelTemplate = nr.AntennaPanel([4,4], elements=elementTemplate, polarization=\"+\")\n",
    "\n",
    "# Now we can create the antenna array using the panel template. Note that the spacing values are \n",
    "# multiples of the wavelength\n",
    "antennaArray = nr.AntennaArray([2,2], spacing=[3,3], panels=panelTemplate)\n",
    "\n",
    "# The 'showElements' method draws the antenna array, showing all panels and elements.\n",
    "antennaArray.showElements(zeroTicks=True)\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "id": "1a973b7a",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 600x600 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Depending on the input parameters, the drawRadiation method can generate different types of plots. \n",
    "# Here, we plot the antenna’s directivity in the horizontal plane at zero elevation.\n",
    "radValues = antennaArray.drawRadiation(theta=90, radiationType=\"Directivity\", normalize=False)\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "id": "d19a36e7",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 600x600 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Here, the 'drawRadiation' method is used to plot the radiation power in the vertical plane at an azimuth angle of 0°.\n",
    "radValues = antennaArray.drawRadiation(phi=0, radiationType=\"PowerDb\", normalize=False)\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "id": "853b2495",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1000x1000 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# Here, the 'drawRadiation' method is used to generate a 3D plot of directivity.\n",
    "radValues = antennaArray.drawRadiation(radiationType=\"Directivity\", normalize=True, \n",
    "                                       viewAngles=(30,10), figSize=10)"
   ]
  },
